2. The Ordinations at the Ember &asom—that is, of Priests and Deacons.

The ordinations of deacons and priests were also per- formed with a very simple ritual, but they were celebrated with great publicity at a solemn station. There was not an ordination every year, but when the necessity arose one of the Saturdays of the Ember weeks was always chosen.2

The candidates for ordination, chosen by the pope, were at first presented to the faithful during the Stational Masses of Wednesday and Friday in Santa Maria Maggiore and in the Church of the Holy Apostles.
